==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*aitra-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[ettor]] (Dutch [[etter#Dutch|etter]] ‘pus’), Old High German [[eitar]] (German [[Eiter]] ‘pus’), Old Norse [[eitr]] (Swedish [[etter#Swedish|etter]]).

